# SCSS @font-face mixin

This node module font-face started to make my work easier. Instead of find & copy & paste base64 encrypted fonts for each and every project I just @include them using this SCSS mixin.  

## Install
1. `yarn add font-face` or `npm install --save-dev font-face` 
2. Import it into your SCSS code:
```scss
@import "font-face";
```
3. Include required fonts
```scss
@include font-face('Roboto', 100, normal);
@include font-face('Roboto Condensed', 300, normal);
```

## Output
```css
@font-face {
  font-family: "Roboto";
  font-weight: 100;
  font-style: normal;
  font-stretch: normal;
  src: local('Roboto Thin'), local('Roboto-Thin'), url(data:application/font-woff2;charset=utf-8;base64,) format('woff2'), url(data:application/font-woff;charset=utf-8;base64,) format('woff');
  font-display: swap;
}

@font-face {
  font-family: "Roboto Condensed";
  font-weight: 300;
  font-style: normal;
  font-stretch: normal;
  src: local('Roboto Condensed Light'), local('RobotoCondensed-Light'), url(data:application/font-woff2;charset=utf-8;base64,) format('woff2'), url(data:application/font-woff;charset=utf-8;base64,) format('woff');
  font-display: swap;
}
```

## Included fonts
- Arvo
- Montserrat
- Open Sans
- Open Sans Condensed
- PT Sans
- Roboto
- Roboto Condensed
- Roboto Slab
- 

## Resources
- Download fonts via [http://google-webfonts-helper.herokuapp.com/fonts](http://google-webfonts-helper.herokuapp.com/fonts)
- Convert to base64 encrypted [https://jaicab.com/localFont/](https://jaicab.com/localFont/)

## Bonus tip
Create a separate font.scss where you include your fonts and serve it using localstorage as mentioned on [https://jaicab.com/localFont/](https://jaicab.com/localFont/)
